it's just like 2.13
when we want to find commit we have two way
1.relative way (by HEAD)
2.direct way (by id(hash))

git show HEAD~1     //show changes

git show HEAD~1:src/section_3/"formatting log command 3"        //use directory (should write based on current path)
                                                                //we can see full final version of that file on this specific version!


git show HEAD~1 --name-only         //just see name of the files
                                    //that has been modified on this specific commit

git show HEAD~1 --name-status       //just see name of the files
                                    //and the status of the changes,
                                    //like A for adding
                                    //like M for modifying

Note: this status study the commit, study the repository!
      the "git status" just study the stage area!